This paper is primarily focused on the application of deep reinforcement learning and curiosity-driven exploration, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also utilizes attention mechanisms, which is a popular technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of curiosity-driven exploration in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a new curiosity formulation, which could potentially fall under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
